Interestingly, SM4 showed the highest values of VOC among all dyes, including N-719. Due to the site-selective adsorption behavior of the SM4, the adsorption of prepared SM4 may form a better dye coverage to help to passivate the TiO2 surface or form an insulating molecular layer composed of prepared dye and thus reduces the recombination due to electron back-transfer between TiO2 and I3-/I-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
